    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The culture and style of the Celtiberians, a Celtic people of the Iberian Peninsula in the final centuries BCE who spoke the Celtiberian language. Archaeologically, the Celtiberians participated in the Hallstatt culture in what is now north-central Spain. Extant tribal names include the Arevaci, Belli, Titti, Lusones, and Berones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
